						               													<description>A two-player strategic game designed by N&amp;eacute;stor Romeral Andr&amp;eacute;s and Jos&amp;eacute; Manuel Astilleros Garc&amp;iacute;a-Monge.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Abstrakto is a game of territorial occupation in which players try to claim territory on the board by closing off empty areas with three different types of tiles (&amp;ldquo;Solid&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Line&amp;rdquo;, and &amp;ldquo;Cross&amp;rdquo;) according to simple placement rules. A closed area is conquered by the player with most tiles surrounding it.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; A 7 &amp;times; 7 square board&amp;#10;    &amp;bull; 18 blue tiles (6 of each type) &amp;#10;    &amp;bull; 18 orange tiles (6 of each type)&amp;#10;    &amp;bull; 25 scoring markers (10 blue and 10 orange and 5 grey)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Solid&amp;rdquo; tiles can only be placed inside the board cells.&amp;#10;      &amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Line&amp;rdquo; tiles can only be placed centered on the edges of the board cells, including the edge of the board.&amp;#10;      &amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Cross&amp;rdquo; tiles can only be placed on the lines&amp;rsquo; intersections, excluding the edge and the corner of the board (in those places, the tile&amp;rsquo;s lines would extend beyond the underlying gridlines of the cell borders).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
